  "commentary": "With SPX at 6602.6 sitting just above the massive +7429.9M gamma wall at 6600 and below the 6610 flip strike, dealers are in active selling mode to hedge their long gamma position as spot pushes through this key resistance. The wall_break and gex_surge events indicate we've just penetrated the 6600 level with significant options flow, but the PIN regime suggests dealers will aggressively sell any further upside momentum above 6610 while providing strong support at the 6600 level on pullbacks. Watch for mean reversion behavior between 6600-6610 as the current level sits in dealer selling territory, with 6500 as the critical amplifying level where dealer buying would kick in if we see a larger selloff.\n\nBottom line: expect choppy action with upside capped near 6610 and strong support at 6600.",
